00:37:11.350 --> 00:37:15.300
So now we're talking
about a different process.

00:37:15.300 --> 00:37:18.730
We were talking before
about electrons.

00:37:18.730 --> 00:37:21.515
They're starting up in a higher
energy level, going lower.

00:37:21.515 --> 00:37:23.160
But with photon
absorption, we're

00:37:23.160 --> 00:37:27.240
going the other direction, so
we're going from a lower state.

00:37:27.240 --> 00:37:28.860
We're being excited.

00:37:28.860 --> 00:37:31.760
They're absorbing energy
and being excited,

00:37:31.760 --> 00:37:35.420
so we can have a final
state that is higher,

00:37:35.420 --> 00:37:39.505
and the energy is gained in this
process, so it's being excited.

00:37:43.011 --> 00:37:43.510
All right.

00:37:43.510 --> 00:37:45.370
So we can think about
the same things,

00:37:45.370 --> 00:37:48.190
then, in terms of absorption.

00:37:48.190 --> 00:37:51.430
So if we have a big
energy difference,

00:37:51.430 --> 00:37:57.160
if it's absorbing a lot of
energy, big energy difference,

00:37:57.160 --> 00:38:01.780
it's going to be absorbing
light with a high frequency

00:38:01.780 --> 00:38:04.210
and a short wavelength.

00:38:04.210 --> 00:38:06.680
If there's a small
energy difference,

00:38:06.680 --> 00:38:12.370
it'll absorb a photon with a low
frequency or a long wavelength.

00:38:12.370 --> 00:38:14.570
And we'll come back to
