00:39:20.841 --> 00:39:21.340
OK.

00:39:21.340 --> 00:39:25.720
So let's consider the summary
of both of these things now.

00:39:25.720 --> 00:39:28.910
So we're talking about
admission versus absorption.

00:39:28.910 --> 00:39:31.090
And so we have this
Rydberg formula,

00:39:31.090 --> 00:39:33.590
which is what this
is called, and it

00:39:33.590 --> 00:39:36.220
can be used to
calculate the frequency

00:39:36.220 --> 00:39:42.370
of either emitted photons
or absorbed photons, so

00:39:42.370 --> 00:39:44.450
from either process.

00:39:44.450 --> 00:39:46.490
And if we want to
make it more general,

00:39:46.490 --> 00:39:48.600
again, it's just a
one electron case,

00:39:48.600 --> 00:39:53.530
but we can put our z in
for any one electron ion.

00:39:53.530 --> 00:39:57.910
So frequency equals Z squared,
Rydberg constant over Planck's

00:39:57.910 --> 00:40:04.780
constant, and we have 1 over
the final minus initial,

00:40:04.780 --> 00:40:08.450
or initial minus final,
depending on which

00:40:08.450 --> 00:40:10.730
process you're talking about.

00:40:10.730 --> 00:40:14.730
And over here, we'd be
talking, then, about emission.

00:40:14.730 --> 00:40:19.612
So our initial energy is
higher going to lower,

00:40:19.612 --> 00:40:21.070
and when that
happens, you're going

00:40:21.070 --> 00:40:26.470
to be releasing light with
the energy difference that

00:40:26.470 --> 00:40:30.460
is due to the difference
between these states.

00:40:30.460 --> 00:40:32.630
So we're going to
have our electron is

00:40:32.630 --> 00:40:35.220
going to emit this energy.

00:40:35.220 --> 00:40:38.690
In the absorption process
for this equation,

00:40:38.690 --> 00:40:41.910
we're going to go from
an initial state that's

00:40:41.910 --> 00:40:45.020
lower to a higher state.

00:40:45.020 --> 00:40:49.110
So we'll have a final state
that's higher than initial.

00:40:49.110 --> 00:40:50.020
That's absorption.

00:40:50.020 --> 00:40:51.190
It's absorbing energy.

00:40:51.190 --> 00:40:54.450
It's getting excited,
and so the electron

00:40:54.450 --> 00:40:58.490
is absorbing that energy.

00:40:58.490 --> 00:41:01.850
So this really summarizes,
now, what we need

00:41:01.850 --> 00:41:04.820
to know about binding energies.

00:41:04.820 --> 00:41:07.570
Schroedinger equation
also tells us

